                                                                                                                       7                                      Smith, Van Zyl till 2011 Cup
                      
	Johannesburg: South Africa captain Graeme Smith and interim coach Corrie van Zyl were appointed Friday to lead South Africa until after next years World Cup.         
	Cricket South Africa announced after a board meeting that the pair would stay in charge until April 2011. Jacques Kallis will be Smiths deputy in all forms of the game for this period. (AFP)                                                                                                                     
